                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221 Dahl, Harold/31: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-20T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 20, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 20—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My August 4, noon, Harold Dahl. Commanding General, Seville, today expressed firm
                    opinion that Dahl would not be shot even though tried but would be
                    exchanged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
